The paper deals with watermarking medical images, which involves image processing and computer vision techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper uses deep neural networks for recognition tasks, which falls under the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also deals with confidentiality and security of medical information, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The proposed framework involves iterative embedding and extraction processes, which can be considered as a machine learning task, and hence, the paper can also be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper involves the use of ROI maps, which is a common technique in image retrieval and indexing, and hence, the paper can also be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
